sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.username 
FROM users 
JOIN bookings ON users.user_id = bookings.user_id;

SELECT name, neighbourhood_cleansed, city, price
FROM properties
WHERE price > (SELECT AVG(price) FROM properties);

external_knowledge:
- "keepers" refers to 'property owners' in the domain of real estate;
- "under the spotlight" metaphorically refers to the reviews;
- "voices of active owners" refers to active user accounts with the role 'property owner'.

- "travelers about to embark on their next journey" refers to users who have a subsequent booking date;
- "properties they are sailing on to" metaphorically refers to the properties they are booking for their next stay;
- "subsequent departure dates" refers to the start dates of their next bookings.

sql:
SELECT property_id, name, weekly_price
FROM properties
WHERE weekly_price > (SELECT AVG(weekly_price) FROM properties);

SELECT T1.name AS property_name, T2.username AS owner_name
FROM properties AS T1
INNER JOIN users AS T2 ON T1.owner_id = T2.user_id;
